      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested; all from production lot with full device history records. Dimensional inspection confirmed conformance to design drawings. Samples distributed across two independent laboratories to assess inter-laboratory variability."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios or justify single-condition testing with sensitivity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration at 5 mm/min crosshead speed. No variation in offset distance or loading rate explored. Sensitivity analysis not performed for loading rate effects. This factor is below the required level; compensating controls include multi-laboratory replication."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
